.TH "xprt_rdma_close" 9 "xprt_rdma_close" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xprt_rdma_close \- close a transport connection
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" xprt_rdma_close
.BI "(struct rpc_xprt *xprt "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "xprt" 12
transport context
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Called during autoclose or device removal.

Caller holds \fIxprt\fP's send lock to prevent activity on this
transport while the connection is torn down.
